    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Typefaces that slant upward to the right rather than being erect, often having cursive features derived from humanistic cursive script. Most often designed to accompany a roman typeface but sometimes independent.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor lettertypen die eerder schuin naar rechts overhellen dan recht overeind staan, en daardoor verwantschap vertonen met cursieve humanistische schriften. Meestal komen ze voor met een Romaans lettertype, maar soms  ook op zichzelf staand.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>稍微向右傾斜的字體，通常具有人文主義草寫體特色。大多設計來襯托羅馬字體，但有時亦可獨立使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
